1) O'Leary -   Yellow/Brown Sweet Cap  350-460 Fact #30 NO PRINT BACK! printer's scrap SGC LABELED AS "COLOR VARIATION"-     HUGE BORDERS!


$1,100.00 

some brief history of these "type of scraps"::)

OLEARY ON HOLD

  this card is a part of approx. 75 known "yellow browns"( as they are called )printer's scrap.....there are approx. 34 known examples/players that have been identified so far identified by Chris Brown......These cards were the first "recognized" legit scraps/missing colors many years ago.......looks like there were 1 or 2 of these scrap sheets that survived the garbage over 100 years ago! they are very dramatic and are missing almost all the color passes except yellow/red/brown.....hence the nickname "yellow/brown's" for short.......they are also missing the overprint strike on the back to block out the factory # 30 designation.......the bar wasn't simply offset, it just wasn't printed!  card is missing many facets of the normal printing process.......these two sheets were probably scrapped by the printer because of the incompleteness for some reason.......

INTERESTING FACT- there are the same number of players known directly correlated to the BROADLEAF 460 BACK! suggesting these cards were printed simultaneously with the BROADLEAF 460 BACK! (this is not proven yet, but evidence is leaning towards this so far.....these cards are just as rare as the broadleaf 460 cards in every way.....not only are they cool, rare, and scarce.....a really great endeavor would be to collect all 34 players known ! that would be a feat, considering there are only approx 1-5 examples of each of the 34 playes known to exist! (Mcintyre which I will be listing is an example where there are only 1 example known to exist! 


get an example at 1/5 th the price of a broadleaf 460!
